      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): respect models.mode=replace in 'openclaw models list' output",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen `models.mode: \"replace\"` is set with a restricted `models.providers` list, `openclaw models list` still shows models from built-in provider catalogs and authenticated-but-unconfigured providers.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/commands/models/list.list-command.ts`: Added `modelsModeReplace` flag; fixed `enableSourcePlanCascade` to not be blocked by replace mode, so `--all` and `--provider` browse work regardless of `models.mode`\n- `src/commands/models/list.rows.ts`: `appendAuthenticatedCatalogRows` skips processing when in replace mode\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** When `models.mode: \"replace\"` is set, `openclaw models list` no longer shows models from built-in provider catalogs or authenticated-but-unconfigured providers. Explicit `--all` and `--provider <id>` browsing continues to work in replace mode, matching the documented CLI contract.\n\n**Code change rationale:** The initial PR incorrectly blocked `enableSourcePlanCascade` with `!modelsModeReplace`, which prevented `--all` and provider-filtered catalog browsing. The replace-mode restriction is now scoped to `appendAuthenticatedCatalogRows` only.\n\nCloses #94705\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94705-models-mode---replace--does-no",
